<paragraph blockId="24.[136,1452,236,295]" pageId="24" pageNumber="40">
Remarks. Although the 
<typeStatus box="[444,500,237,261]" pageId="24" pageNumber="40">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yin, Bao &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="1995" box="[537,634,237,260]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Lycosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[537,634,237,260]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="40">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were not examined, it is clear that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barrion, Barrion-Dupo &amp; Heong" authorityYear="2012" box="[1012,1173,236,260]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Lycosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hawigvittata">
<emphasis box="[1012,1173,236,260]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="40">L. hawigvittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yin, Bao &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="1995" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Lycosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="40">L. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the original descriptions by Yin, Bao &amp; Zhang (1995).
</paragraph>
